<br>
So I was wondering, What would you suggest to get the warrior back into the swing of things? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utiejinnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/8/02 7:25:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1238.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homex.coolconnect.com/member3/Tiejinnie/images/Avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Warrior.</span><hr size=1> hehe, <br>
