</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umowgley.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mowgley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/9/02 8:26:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1238.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Warrior.</span><hr size=1> the bazaar makes sure that any bottom feeder can get pretty nice twink gear cheap.<br>
<br>
Be better than a bottom feeder and play the warrior with gear near to his level.  Learn what a tank can do and not do, dont get him post 50 gear and never see what playing that level is like. <br>
<br>
A monk is melee, but not a warrior.  Thats not a cut, trust me I would rather have a 52 Monk sometimes than my warrior, but the struggle and the challenge of playing the class is the reward for playing it. <br>
<br>
I guess, in a round about way, I am telling you to get gear near the level of the character so that you ACTUALLY see what its like to play a warrior, not what its like to play a nicely twinked warrior.<br>
<br>
There is a huge difference, suffer a bit then upgrade...you wont be sorry and will appreciate all the things being said on this forum more. <p>-Strongtooth, 52 Iksar Champion<BR>
- Bristlebane Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/9/02 8:35:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1238.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Warrior.</span><hr size=1> To re-equip a 39 warrior, the bazaar is definitely your friend.  You should be able to get a full suit of crusty or crafted for about 1k and some decent weapons for a bit more (the Str/Sta of crusty is porbably better for a halfling).  A haste item would be nice but don't sweat it, you can live without it.<br>
<br>
Look for cheap, preferably fast weapons and work up any skills that your friend did not work on.  Good weapons are the Centis - Short sword, Warhammer, and Spear, they are all cheap and work well.  Get a Sarnak Battlehammer, 30/40 2hb, goes for about 100pp on Sol Ro and work on 2hb.<br>
<br>
My advice, getting all your weapon skills maxed in the 40s is more important than having big weapons that kick a lot of butt.  Sure Wurmys do nice damage, but having maxed skills in the 50s when you start to get access to a lot of very sweet weapons is probably a much better long-term decision. <p>Hyardgune Varangian <BR> 57 Ogre Myrmidon of Gathered Might</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showPrevMessage?topicID=1238.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showNextMessage?topicID=1238.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1238.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.emailToFriend?topicID=1238.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.threadControl?topicID=1238.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1238.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1238.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><tab